.TH "s3c_pm_do_restore_core" 9 "s3c_pm_do_restore_core" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
s3c_pm_do_restore_core \- early restore register values from save list.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" s3c_pm_do_restore_core
.BI "(const struct sleep_save *ptr "  ","
.BI "int count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ptr" 12
Pointer to an array of registers.
.IP "count" 12
Size of the ptr array.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is similar to \fBs3c_pm_do_restore\fP except we try and minimise the
side effects of the function in case registers that hardware might need
to work has been restored.

WARNING: Do not put any debug in here that may effect memory or use
peripherals, as things may be changing!
